    "body": "`spack build-env` is not respecting `target=` specifier when setting up the build environment.\r\n\r\nUsing:\r\n* `spack@develop`\r\n* 35511c178bddbb228ee5852e4842f9043943e7df\r\n* `Sat Nov 14 23:45:10 2020 +0800`\r\n\r\n```\r\n$> spack build-env py-tensorflow+rocm~cuda~nccl target=x86_64 ^python@3 ^py-h5py~mpi ^hdf5~mpi\r\n==> Warning: gcc@7.5.0 cannot build optimized binaries for \"zen2\". Using best target possible: \"zen\"\r\n==> Error: Unable to locate perl command in /opt/spack/opt/spack/linux-ubuntu18.04-zen/gcc-7.5.0/perl-5.32.0-bhiayj3jmqk2n5qc2q7wpxh2snm6n3ry/bin\r\n```",
